For $b > 0$, $b \neq 1$, and positive numbers $M$ and $N$:

$$\begin{aligned}
 \log_b(MN) &= \log_b M + \log_b N && \text{(Product Rule)} \label{eq:log-product}\\[0.5em]
 \log_b\left(\frac{M}{N}\right) &= \log_b M - \log_b N && \text{(Quotient Rule)} \label{eq:log-quotient}\\[0.5em]
 \log_b(M^p) &= p \cdot \log_b M && \text{(Power Rule)} \label{eq:log-power}
\end{aligned}$$
